{"actual_usd":0.124645,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":151,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24476,"reply":"\"No... I don't think that's the shape of it.\" *I rub a thumb through the flour on my apron and glance toward the oven mouth, where the heat keeps breathing steady.* \"Less sent, maybe. Less lowered, for a time. But not less God.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, thinking it through plain.* \"When Christ says the Father is greater, I hear greatness of place, of sending, of station in that moment — not a smaller divinity, like God comes in slices. And the Spirit—\" *I give a small shake of my head.* \"—isn't the runt of the family. Same holiness. Same God. Different person, different work, no lesser glory.\"","rolling_24h_usd":32.33262000000002,"run_id":"e85b2be5-03da-4a2a-8707-b22b179fc234"}
